# Client Project Structure

This document describes the folder and file organization for the React client application.

---

## Root Structure

```
client/
├── .claude/              # Claude-specific agent documentation
│   └── docs/             # Source of truth for all patterns
├── public/               # Static assets served directly
├── src/                  # Main source code
├── tasks/                # Agent task outputs
├── index.html            # Entry HTML file
├── package.json          # Dependencies and scripts
├── tsconfig.json         # TypeScript configuration
├── vite.config.ts        # Vite bundler configuration
└── vitest.config.ts      # Test runner configuration
```

---

## Source Code Structure (`src/`)

```
src/
├── api/                  # API client and request utilities
├── components/           # Reusable UI components
│   ├── ui/               # shadcn/ui primitives (button, input, etc.)
│   └── [Feature]/        # Feature-specific components
├── context/              # React Context providers
├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks
├── lib/                  # Utility functions and helpers
├── pages/                # Page-level components (route targets)
├── routes/               # React Router configuration
├── App.tsx               # Root application component
├── main.tsx              # Application entry point
└── index.css             # Global styles (Tailwind imports)
```

---

## Folder Conventions

### Components (`src/components/`)

- Each component lives in its own folder: `ComponentName/`
- Folder contains:
  - `ComponentName.tsx` — main component file
  - `index.ts` — re-exports the component
  - `__tests__/` — test files (if applicable)

Example:

```
components/
└── Sidebar/
    ├── Sidebar.tsx
    ├── SidebarNavigation.tsx
    ├── SidebarHeader.tsx
    ├── SidebarFooter.tsx
    ├── index.ts
    └── __tests__/
        └── Sidebar.test.tsx
```

### Pages (`src/pages/`)

- Each page lives in its own folder: `PageName/`
- Folder contains:
  - `PageName.tsx` — main page component
  - `index.ts` — re-exports the page
  - `__tests__/` — test files (if applicable)

Example:

```
pages/
└── Dashboard/
    ├── Dashboard.tsx
    ├── index.ts
    └── __tests__/
        └── Dashboard.test.tsx
```

### Hooks (`src/hooks/`)

- Custom hooks are placed directly in `hooks/` folder
- Naming convention: `use<HookName>.ts`

Example:

```
hooks/
├── useSidebar.ts
├── useAuth.ts
└── useTransactions.ts
```

### Context (`src/context/`)

- Context providers are placed in `context/` folder
- Naming convention: `<ContextName>Context.tsx`

Example:

```
context/
├── AuthContext.tsx
├── SidebarContext.tsx
└── ThemeContext.tsx
```

### API (`src/api/`)

- API utilities and request functions
- Organized by domain or feature

Example:

```
api/
├── client.ts             # Axios or fetch wrapper
├── auth.ts               # Auth-related API calls
├── transactions.ts       # Transaction API calls
└── categories.ts         # Category API calls
```

---

## Naming Conventions

| Type           | Convention         | Example                  |
| -------------- | ------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Components     | PascalCase         | `Sidebar.tsx`            |
| Hooks          | camelCase with use | `useSidebar.ts`          |
| Context        | PascalCase         | `SidebarContext.tsx`     |
| Utilities      | camelCase          | `formatCurrency.ts`      |
| Test files     | Same as source     | `Sidebar.test.tsx`       |
| Index files    | lowercase          | `index.ts`               |
| CSS/Style      | kebab-case         | `sidebar-styles.css`     |
| Constants      | SCREAMING_SNAKE    | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`        |
| Type/Interface | PascalCase         | `SidebarProps`           |
| Enum           | PascalCase         | `TransactionType`        |
| Folder         | PascalCase         | `Sidebar/`, `Dashboard/` |

---

## File Extensions

| Extension | Usage                            |
| --------- | -------------------------------- |
| `.tsx`    | React components with JSX        |
| `.ts`     | TypeScript without JSX           |
| `.css`    | Stylesheets                      |
| `.test.tsx` / `.test.ts` | Test files          |

---

## Import Conventions

- Use absolute imports with `@/` prefix
- Example: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'`

---

## Test Placement

- Tests are placed in `__tests__/` folder next to the code they test
- Test file naming: `<ComponentName>.test.tsx`

---

## Notes

- `ui/` folder contains shadcn/ui primitives — do not modify directly
- Feature components should be self-contained in their own folders
- Shared utilities go in `lib/`
- Page-specific logic stays within the page folder
